titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Collection of Spanish Bookplates
titlestmt.author: Compiled by Christian Vazquez and Nathaniel Dolquist

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Saturday December 8, 2018 at 00:03

did.abstract: The collection contains examples of bookplates by Spanish artists as well as those commissioned by Spanish patrons.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011, it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Collection of Spanish Bookplates, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Some materials included in this collection indicate the provenance of the following collectors: A. Bernard C. K. Keeves, Baron Gunnar de Trönnberg, and Bernhard Bergl.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains examples of historical and modern Spanish bookplates. These ex-libris are either by Spanish artists or commissioned by Spanish patrons.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: I. Bookplates – Artists & Individuals. II. Bookplates – To be filed. III. Bookplates – Miscellaneous. IV. Bookplates – Barcelona.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged alphabetically by the artist's or individual's last name. Artists' folders are separated and marked as such, as per the original order. Please note that the separation of artists and patrons may, on occasion, interrupt the alphabetical ordering of the series.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains bookplates previously housed in a folder marked "To be filed, A-L and L-Z."

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged alphabetically by patron's last name.

did.unittitle: Casal – Marques de la Fuensanta del Xalle

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains various groupings of bookplates, including royal Spanish examples, Spanish and Portuguese materials from the A. Bernard C. K. Keeves collection, and universal as well as some unidentified bookplate specimens.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains materials that were grouped together in a file labeled "Barcelona." It includes inventories, exchange requests with accompanying bookplates, and bookplate portfolios and related ephemera from the 1958 Ex-Libris Congress held in Barcelona.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Folio contains an inventory and 60-plus bookplates designed for Pepita Pallé by various artists, dating from 1946-1962.
